// =============================================================================
// core/security/sig/mod.vr — Non-elliptic signature schemes
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Security / Sig
// =============================================================================
//
// Non-EC signature schemes. Elliptic-curve signature schemes
// (Ed25519, ECDSA-P256) live under `core.security.ecc`. This
// umbrella covers the historical RSA family + V1.5 follow-ups
// (DSA, post-quantum signature schemes once `core.security.pq`
// stabilises its primitives).
//
//   * `rsa.vr` — RSA signatures + PKCS#1 v1.5 / PSS encodings.
//                Required for X.509 / TLS / SSH interop and for
//                JWS RS256 / PS256 token signing. Constant-time
//                blinded modular exponentiation prevents timing
//                channels through the private key.
//
// New users should prefer `core.security.ecc.ed25519` over RSA
// when both endpoints support it — Ed25519 has smaller keys,
// faster verification, and no PKCS#1 padding-oracle footguns.
// RSA stays here for legacy / interop reasons.
// =============================================================================

module core.security.sig;

public module rsa;
